<font color="#FF0000">ANYBODY KNOW MY DAD?</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jan  3 15:12:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
 My name is a Jim Truxal.I'm trying to find someone who<br>
knew my father, Paul James Truxal. He served in viet Nam<br>
in '62-'63. He was in the Air Force at &quot;Monkey Mountain&quot;.<br>
He didn't talk much about his time there. I do know he<br>
helped an Army helo crew by manning a door gun. He was <br>
wounded and as far as I can tell was awarded a Purple Heart<br>
by the Army.The Air Force then Court Martialled him for<br>
endangering gov't property (himself) and took the medal away. He had another Purple Heart from WWII.<br>
 He served in the Navy and was in WWII and Korea before<br>
going into the Air Force.I know he was on the Grady(?)<br>
DE445.I think he worked with power production and also<br>
powered AGE equipment while in Viet Nam.He was a trainer<br>
at Sheppard AFB either just before or just after his time<br>
in Nam. He retired in '65 (he was at Lockbourne AFB then).<br>
 He died of cancer in '82.Three wars,various accidents,bouts<br>
with alcohol didn't kill him.Too bad he couldn't have died of old age and seen my kids.Sometimes life sucks.<br>
 If any of you knew him, I'd appreciate hearing from you.<br><br>
 He grew up around the Pittsburgh/Greensburg Pa. area.
